).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[166,794,1368,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,274,1368,1392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hill, 1919" authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1919" box="[292,570,1368,1392]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Sargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gselli">
<emphasis box="[292,442,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Sargus gselli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hill, G. F." box="[452,570,1368,1392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" pagination="450 - 462" refId="ref11189" refString="Hill, G. F. 1919. Australian Stratiomyidae (Diptera), with description of new species. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales 44: 450 - 462." type="journal article" year="1919">Hill, 1919</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kertesz" authorityYear="1912" box="[166,330,1398,1422]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Cephalochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[166,330,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Cephalochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing the following: head being much wider than high, ocelli forming an equilateral triangle and occiput without a posteriorly projecting fringe of hair-like setae. The general appearance of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1919" box="[505,585,1486,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Sargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gselli">
<emphasis box="[505,585,1486,1510]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">S. gselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely similar to other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kertesz" authorityYear="1912" box="[391,559,1515,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Cephalochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[391,559,1515,1539]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Cephalochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from Pacific islands, as well as the 
<typeStatus box="[409,455,1545,1569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
species. Therefore, we transfer this species from its previous position in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[604,677,1574,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Sargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[604,677,1574,1597]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Sargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to become 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hill, 1919)" authorityName="Lessard &amp; Yeates &amp; Woodley" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[166,511,1603,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Cephalochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gselli" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[166,385,1603,1627]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Cephalochrysa gselli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hill, G. F." box="[398,503,1603,1627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" pagination="450 - 462" refId="ref11189" refString="Hill, G. F. 1919. Australian Stratiomyidae (Diptera), with description of new species. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales 44: 450 - 462." type="journal article" year="1919">Hill, 1919</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[516,634,1603,1627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[516,634,1603,1627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kertesz" authorityYear="1912" box="[195,356,1632,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Cephalochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[195,356,1632,1656]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Cephalochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[420,521,1632,1656]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
